nodes.title: Motion Core Instructions
widgets_values:
█▚▞▌ ⬤ ▀█▀ █ ⬤ █▚▌ ◖ ⬤ ◤▄ █☰
Version 1.0 

An experimental animation synthesizer.

Most ComfyUI workflows are developed to create specific types of output. This system was designed to function more like a synthesizer capable of accepting multiple types of inputs, generations and outputs. Experiment and see what you can create! 

Instructions:
1. Write a prompt (or let the prompt expander help you).
2. Choose an input (generate an image, input an external image, input an external video)
3. Choose your video output (Preview, Upscaled, Interpolated).
4. Choose which controlnets best apply to your input. Adjust weights to get wildly different results. 
5. Enable Video IPAdapter and adjust weights to stylize the video. Disable Video IPAdapter to use only the Sampling prompt as style input.
6. Choose the resolution of the preview video as well as the final interpolated output.
7. Set your framerates. Higher framerates will take longer to render. Lower framerates will result in less continuity in interpolation stage. 
8. Attach the appropriate "IPAdapter Input" and "Control Input" connections. 


Performance:
◘ Designed for an Nvidia 4090 GPU with 24GB of VRAM. Anything with less than 24GB of VRAM may show errors in certain configurations. 
◘ If you're getting errors, it's likely that you're running out of VRAM.
◘ Try inputting and generating smaller video clips (length and resolution).  
◘ Turning off any inputs, outputs or controlnets that you don't currently need will also save on VRAM usage. 


Usage Notes:
◘ If the full graph isn't updating when you queue prompt, change the animation seed or batch size by 1 and prompt again.
◘ Any nodes that you may need to adjust are green and located to the left of the preview videos.
◘ If you just want to explore image generation, disconnect the lines in the "IPAdapter Input" and "Control Input" groups.
◘ If video is looking "burned" adjust the CFG Rescale. The more control nets used the more this may need to be adjusted. 
◘ When enabling "Video input adjustments", the invert switch will be enabled by default. Select the node and hit Ctrl-B to disable. 
◘ When swapping checkpoint models, make sure to check civit.ai for the best sampler settings for each model. 
◘ Some models are better than others for animation purposes.


Questions, suggestions and feedback: ratliff@adobe.com

nodes.title: Release notes
widgets_values:
V 1.0 Release Notes:
  ○ Welcome to V1 of The Motion Core Workflow! This is the culmination of three weeks of work.
  ○ I will continue to expand and update as I run into limitations for my current animation project.

Coming soon:
  ○ Foreground / background video combine
  ○ Controllable video segmentation and masking. 
  ○ Segmentation for 2D and 3D render passes. 
  ○ Face Restore
